					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex; Italian semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex. </support>
								<extent>298 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>400</height>
										<width>250</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>265</height>
										<width>180</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p> 298 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>31 quires: i2 (folios 1-2), ii-xvii10 (folios 3-162), xviii8 (folios 163-170), xix-xxx10 (folios 171-290), xxxi8 (folios 291-298).  </p>
									<p>Catchwords. </p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="52" writtenLines="52">
									<p>Pricking and ruling are visible. </p>
									<p>Words deleted (e. g., folios 9r, 15r, 17v, 36r, 47r, 70v, 82v, 145v, 160r, 249v, 269r).  </p>
									<p>Rewritten parts (e. g., folios 4r, 139v, 143v, 266r).  </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary/>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
								<p>Italian semi-cursive script, unpunctuated.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="scribe">Yeḳuti᾿el ben Shelomoh</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, 28 Sivan [5]134 [1374] (folio 298v ); Yeḳuti᾿el is marked off in the initial letters of the lines (folio 84v). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Menaḥem ben Natan</name>, first owner: inscribed with his name in the colophon, 28 Sivan [5]134 [1374] (folio 298v). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Hananel Menaḥem ben Yehi᾿el</name> sold to <name type="person" role="owner">Mosheh ben Yosef</name>: inscribed with their name in a purchase note, 2 December, [5]192 [1432] (folio 2r, upside down). </p>
							<p>Shelomoh ben Shim῾on: inscribed with his name as witness in a purchase note, 2 December, [5]192 [1432] (folio 2r). </p>
							<p>Yom Tov ben Yitsḥaḳ: inscribed with his name as witness in a purchase note, 2 December, [5]192 [1432] (folio 2r). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">David of Ventura</name>owner: a list of manuscripts and printed books owned by him, 1501 (folios 1r, 2r). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yehudah Zeraḥyah ῾Azulai</name>: inscribed with his name, 16th century (folios 1r, 20r). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yosef Yehudah ben Yehudah Zeraḥyah ῾Azulai</name>: inscribed with his name, 16th century (folio 1r). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Shemu᾿el ben Yitsḥaḳ Azari᾿el of Lavolta</name>: inscribed with his name as a missing person, August 1535 (folio 2v ). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person">Menaḥem of Lavolta</name>, Shemu&apos;el’s brother: inscribed with his name, August 1535 (folio 2v). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Mosheh of Lavolta ben Yitsḥaḳ</name>: sold to <name type="person" role="owner">Yosef ben Shelomoh Fo᾿ah</name>: purchase note, 17 November, 1542 (folio 3r). </p>
							<p>Latin inscription, 1556 (folio 3r). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Laurentius Franguellus</name>: inscribed with his name, 1575 (folio 2r ). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Luigi da Bologna</name>: inscribed with his name, 1600 (folio 298v). </p>
						</additions>
